President Muhammadu Buhari has met with the Borno State governor, Babagana Zulum, on the recent Chadian military operation on the Lake Chad Basin. After the meeting, Governor Zulum told State House Correspondents the the military operations may have implications on Nigeria’s national security. Zulum the president has promised to take more decisive and proactive measures towards ensuring that the Boko Haram menace in parts of the country is totally eliminated for sustainable peace and development. He said that “after critically analysing the situation, we both expressed the belief that the time had come to once and for all put an end to the senseless acts of terror by Boko Haram and other criminal elements operating in the region.” LEADERSHIP recalls that the action of the Chadian soldiers was in retaliation over the recent killing of the country’s 91 security personnel by the Boko Haram insurgents.